Rewrote is-countably-presented-closed-×BR to be self-contained and elegant.

Previous version imported Booleω-closed-×BR from ProductClosure and
bridged between is-countably-presented and is-countably-presented-alt.
New version works directly with has-countable-presentation (the untruncated,
Type₁ version with arbitrary countable types), avoiding the ℕ-encoding detour.

Structure:
- has-CS-⊎: countability of A ⊎ B from countability of A and B
- has-CS-Unit: countability of Unit
- ×BR-resp-equiv: product preserves BooleanRingEquiv
- ProductPresentation module (parametric over types A₁, A₂, X₁, X₂):
  - G = A₁ ⊎ (A₂ ⊎ Unit) (generators with idempotent separator)
  - R = (X₁ ⊎ X₂) ⊎ (A₁ ⊎ A₂) (combined relations + orthogonality)
  - rel : R → freeBA G (the relation function)
  - POSTULATE product-equiv : Q ≅ (freeBA A₁ / Im f₁) ×BR (freeBA A₂ / Im f₂)
- Main theorem: clean composition of ×BR-resp-equiv and product-equiv

The postulate product-equiv captures the hard algebraic content
(Chinese Remainder Theorem for Boolean rings via idempotent separator).

File grew from 280 to 402 lines. No useful work lost from previous version
(previous version was a thin wrapper around imports).
